nec edulium = ne edulium quidem. The Jews were forbidden to eat blood, as being the life of the animal which should be offered to God. Similarly the flesh of anim-als killed by suffocation was forbidden as still containing the blood. This prohibition was very ancient, going back to the time of Noah (Gen. 9. 2). In the Mosaic law the prohibition is continued (Lavit. 3. 17 ; 7. 26; 17. 12-14 ; Dent. 12. 16 and 23).
